irreducible. (Image)\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the stage of this patient\u0027s haemorrhoids?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stage I","Stage II","Stage III","Stage IV","Stage V"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has \u003Cstrong\u003EStage IV\u003C/strong\u003E haemorrhoids, which are permanently prolapsed and cannot be reduced manually. The staging of haemorrhoids is as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage I\u003C/strong\u003E haemorrhoids bulge into the anal canal but do not prolapse\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage II\u003C/strong\u003E haemorrhoids prolapse during defaecation but reduce spontaneously\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage III\u003C/strong\u003E haemorrhoids prolapse during defaecation and require manual reduction\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage IV\u003C/strong\u003E haemorrhoids are permanently prolapsed and cannot be reduced\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no \u003Cstrong\u003EStage V\u003C/strong\u003E classification for haemorrhoids. Risk factors include chronic constipation, prolonged straining, pregnancy, and increased intra-abdominal pressure.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Haemorrhoids are classified into four stages based on their degree of prolapse and reducibility","Stage IV haemorrhoids are permanently prolapsed and cannot be reduced manually"],"references":["Mott T, Latimer K, Edwards C. Hemorrhoids: Diagnosis and Treatment Options. Am Fam Physician. 2018 Feb 1;97(3):172-179. PMID: 29431977","Sun Z, Migaly J. Review of Hemorrhoid Disease: Presentation and Management. Clin Colon Rectal Surg. 2016 Mar;29(1):22-9. doi: 10.1055/s-0035-1568144. PMID: 26929748; PMCID: PMC4755769","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48816"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15403"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21202"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21202","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21202"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/GQ4pGPpqQUOg30wsZkImTKaJ0sxMw2.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/GQ4pGPpqQUOg30wsZkImTKaJ0sxMw2.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48816","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48816"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-20T20:23:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-20T20:24:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8094"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63365"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attribut